<TITLE> Local BNP man ordered to surrender in Karwan killing case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 6 (bdnews24.com)The High Court has asked local BNP leader Lutfor Rahman to surrender to a lower court within eight weeks in connection with the triple murders in the capital's Karwan Bazaar last month. Denying Lutfor anticipatory bail for, a two-judge bench of justices Md Abdul Wahab Mia and Abdur Razzaq directed law enforcing agencies not to arrest or harass him in the interim period. Local Awami League leader Mohammed Ashraf Mia, local Jatiya Party leader Faruq Mollah, and Faruq's bodyguard Nuruddin Sarker Jewel died when gunmen opened fire in the middle of Karwan Bazaar, the city's largest open market, on June 26. Faruq Molla's brother Mobarak Hossain filed a case with Tejgaon police on the day accusing Lutfor Rahman, among others. bdnews
